Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportPinAssignStatistics(25.10)              reportPinAssignStatistics(25.10)

Name
       reportPinAssignStatistics  - Generates the pin QoR data for a specified
       partition(s)

Syntax
       reportPinAssignStatistics

       [-help]

       [-maxFanOut <fanOutCount>]

       [-maxRegisterFanOut <registerFanOutCount>]

       [-outFile <pinQoRFileName>]

       [-hinst <hinstNameList> | -ptn <ptnNameList>]

       Generates the pin QoR data for a specified partition(s).

       Note:

              * If a net is  not  routed,  then,  manhattan  distance  between
                source-sink  pairs  is  be used to replace corresponding wire-
                length distance.

              * For floating pins (from outside) of a partition,the pin is al-
                ways assumed to be within the timing cone box.

              * Pin QoR statistics is not generated for blackbox partitions

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each reportPinAssignStatistic parameter. For a de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command: man reportPinAssignStatistic.

       -hinst <hinstNameList>
              Generates  the pin QoR metrics for all pins of the specified hi-
              erarchical instance name or list of instance names.

              Default: All partition and clone hierarchical instances.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -maxFanOut <fanOutCount>
              Specifies the maximum fanout count. The QoR report is not gener-
              ated for a pin if the number of instances  in  its  timing  cone
              fanout exceeds this maximum fanout count,

              Default: 1000

              Data_type: string, optional

       -maxRegisterFanOut <registerFanOutCount>
              Specifies  the  maximum register fanout count. The QoR report is
              not generated for a pin if the number of registers in its timing
              cone fanout exceeds this maximum fanout count.

              Default: 50

              Data_type: string, optional

       -outFile <pinQoRFileName>
              Specifies an output report file for the pin QoR data.

       Default: ./pin_qor.txt

              Data_type: string, optional

       -ptn <ptnNameList>
              Generates the pin QoR metrics for all pins of the  partition  or
              list of partitions.

              Default: All partition and clones.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
              * The following command creates a pin_qor.txt report file:

                reportPinAssignStatistics

              * The following command generates a reference pin QoR file named
                pin_qor_reference.txt.

                reportPinAssignStatistics -outFile pin_qor_reference.txt

              * The  following  command  generates a target pin QoR file named
                pin_qor_target.txt.

                reportPinAssignStatistics -outFile pin_qor_target.txt

